# Estate OS — Cursor Rules
# Cursor reads this file automatically on every session.
# Full specification: Estate-OS-Master-Plan-v2.md in the repo root.
# Read the full master plan before making any architectural decisions.

## How to Work With MHH (read this first)

MHH is not a developer. These behavior rules are non-negotiable:

- SILENT PROBLEM SOLVING. If you hit an error or obstacle, try to fix it yourself first. Only surface it to MHH if you are truly stuck after multiple attempts.
- KEY MILESTONES ONLY. Do not narrate every step. Only report when a major phase completes (e.g. "packages installed", "pipeline ran successfully", "first rows written to sheet"). Skip the play-by-play.
- REAL WRITES: USE JUDGMENT. Run in dry-run mode for anything that touches real data (sheet, Drive, log files). Go live automatically for low-risk steps (installs, config, test runs). Never use --confirm on writes to the real sheet without telling MHH first.
- SAFE BY DEFAULT. Take extra steps to make things debuggable: log errors to file, validate config before running, check dependencies exist before using them. Fail loudly with a plain-English error rather than silently.
- PLAIN ENGLISH ONLY. When you do need to tell MHH something, say it in one or two plain sentences. No jargon, no stack traces unless asked.

## What This Project Is

Estate OS is a personal and family estate operating system with three layers:
1. Ops Ledger (Google Sheet) — non-sensitive daily operations, LLM-visible, append-only
2. Obsidian Vault (local markdown) — dark to all LLMs, institutional memory
3. Gold Vault (Cryptomator-encrypted) — LLMs never read or write

Voice memos from phone → Gemini parses into structured rows → Google Sheet → weekly sync to Obsidian.

Owner: MHH (mhaefele@gmail.com) — non-developer, needs clear microsteps over clever abstractions.
Repo: github.com/mhaefele2312/estate-orchestrator

## Non-Negotiable Rules — violating any is a build-breaking error

1. ZERO LLM WRITE. No LLM writes to any document except appending rows to the Ops Ledger Google Sheet via gspread.append_row(). LLMs never write to Obsidian. LLMs never write to Gold vault. LLMs never modify existing sheet rows.

2. NO SENSITIVITY SCREENING. Do not build any PII detection, content filtering, or bifurcated routing in the capture pipeline. Everything goes to the Ops Ledger. Period.

3. VAULTS ARE DARK. Cloud LLMs never read or write to Obsidian vault or Gold vault. Only future local LLMs (Phase 5+) may access vault data.

4. FAIL-CLOSED. Every script defaults to dry-run mode. Real actions require --confirm flag.

5. APPEND-ONLY. The Ops Ledger sheet is append-only. Flat log files are append-only. Nothing is ever deleted.

6. THREE-STAGE PIPELINE ISOLATION. Stage 2 (Gemini) receives ONLY the raw transcript — never the sheet, never flat files. Stage 2 outputs ONLY JSON. Stage 3 (Python) writes to four targets simultaneously.

7. GEMINI FOR DAILY OPS, CLAUDE FOR BUILDING. Do not build features that use Claude API for daily operations. Gemini handles captures and queries.

## Architecture

Phone → GitHub Pages capture app → raw .md transcript → Google Drive

Laptop Python pipeline:
  Stage 1: Read raw .md (no LLM)
  Stage 2: Gemini API → JSON array of rows
  Stage 3: Python writes to: Google Sheet + flat logs + contacts CSV + contact-mentions.md

Weekly sync: Python pushes logs + SOT snapshots + contact pages → Obsidian

## Sheet Schema (18 columns)

entry_date, entry_time, capture_mode, item_type, domain, description, responsible, due_date, status, notes, source_capture, captured_by, given_name, family_name, organization, title, phone, email

## 12 Domains

01_Financial, 02_Legal, 03_Property, 04_Insurance, 05_Medical, 06_Tax, 07_Estate-Planning, 08_Vehicles, 09_Digital, 10_Family, 11_Contacts, 12_Operations

## Key Dependencies

- gspread — Google Sheets API (append_row for sheet writes)
- google-auth — OAuth for Google APIs
- google-generativeai — Gemini API for capture parsing
- Python 3

## File Paths on the Estate Laptop

Obsidian vault:    C:\Users\mhhro\Documents\Obsidian Vault
Gold vault:        E:\
Gold backup:       G:\My Drive\Gold-Backup
Estate Ops:        G:\My Drive\Estate Ops
MHH Inbox:         G:\My Drive\MHH-Inbox
HBS Inbox:         G:\My Drive\HBS-Inbox
Staging Intake:    G:\My Drive\Staging-Intake
Capture Archive:   G:\My Drive\Capture-Archive

Note: Scripts should use config files or environment variables for paths.

## Output Format — every script must follow this

- DRY RUN: [action that would happen]
- ACTION: [action that was taken]
- ERROR: [what went wrong]
- DONE: [summary at end of every run]

## Code Rules

- Python only. Python 3.10+.
- Every function must have a plain-English docstring.
- Every behavior lives in its own subfolder under behaviors/

## Things NOT to Build

- No sensitivity screening, PII detection, or content filtering
- No bifurcated routing
- No Claude API calls in daily operations
- No Publish behavior development (deferred to Phase 7+)
- No direct LLM writes to Obsidian or Gold vault
- No database — Google Sheets is the database
- No custom UI beyond the capture app

## How to Start a Build Session

1. Read this file
2. Read Estate-OS-Master-Plan-v2.md for full specification
3. Run git log --oneline -20 to see recent work
4. Check what phase we're on by examining existing code
5. Pick up where the last session left off
6. Build one step at a time, show diffs, get approval before moving on
7. MHH is not a developer — give clear microsteps, not abstractions
